    <h1>Girl with a Pearl Earring</h1>

    <p><b>Artist:</b> Johannes Vermeer</p>
    <p><b>Year:</b> 1665</p>
    <p><b>Country:</b> Netherlands</p>
    <p><b>Style:</b> Baroque</p>
    <p><b>Current Location:</b> Mauritshuis Museum, The Hague, Netherlands</p>

    <p>
        Girl with a Pearl Earring is one of Johannes Vermeer's most famous works
        and is often called the "Dutch Mona Lisa." The painting is admired for its
        beautiful use of light, realistic details, and the mystery surrounding the
        identity of the girl in the portrait.
    </p>

